            <h4 style="text-align: center">Factors Determining Car Insurance Premium Calculation </h4>
            <ul>
                <li> <strong>Vehicle Type:</strong> Vehicle Type majorly decides your premium. These factors include the Car Make Model, Motor Transmission type, Car Modification & Car's fuel type.</li>
                <li><strong>Plan Type:</strong> Premium is also determined based on whether you have a Third-Party Car Insurance, a Comprehensive Car Insurance or Standalone Car Insurance.</li>
                <li><strong>Engine's Capacity:</strong> The car’s Cubic capacity also determines the premium for the Own Damage cover.</li>
                <li><strong>Car's IDV:</strong> The sum insured of a comprehensive car insurance policy is its current market value which is called Insured Declared Value (IDV). As your car grows older, the IDV decreases.</li>
                <!--               <li><strong>No Claim Bonus:</strong> NCB discount is availed during policy renewal for zero claims in the previous year. Other factors include Voluntary Deductible, AAI Membership Concessions & Installation of Anti-Theft Devices.</li>-->
                <li><strong>Geographical Location:</strong> Insurance providers also rate the premium according to the place where the insured car will be mostly driven. Urban cities have higher premium rates than rural locations.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
