    <div class="T&C info" id="T&C" style="display:none">
        <h3>Insurance Claim Not Applicable if :</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Driving without a valid license:</strong> If the driver of the vehicle does not have a valid driving license, then any accident or damage caused by that driver may not be covered by the insurance policy.</li>
            <li><strong> Driving under the influence:</strong> If the driver of the vehicle was under the influence of alcohol or drugs at the time of the accident, then the insurance policy may not cover the damages.</li>
            <li><strong>Intentional damage:</strong> If the damage to the vehicle or injury to the third-party was intentionally caused by the policyholder, then the insurance policy may not cover it.</li>
            <li><strong>Using the vehicle for illegal purposes:</strong> If the vehicle was being used for illegal activities at the time of the accident, then the insurance policy may not cover any damages or injuries.</li>
            <li><strong>Failure to report the accident:</strong> If the policyholder fails to report the accident to the insurance company within the stipulated time frame, then the claim may not be accepted.</li>
            <li><strong>Driving outside the policy coverage area:</strong> If the accident or damage occurs outside the geographical limits covered by the insurance policy, then the claim may not be accepted.</li>
            <li><strong>Using the vehicle for commercial purposes:</strong> If the vehicle is being used for commercial purposes and the insurance policy does not cover commercial use, then the claim may not be accepted.</li>
            <li><strong>Age limit:</strong>This insurance policies have age restrictions for the policyholder and/or the driver of the vehicle to be of age 18 or above.</li>
            <li><strong>Excess:</strong> The policyholder may have to pay an excess amount towards the claim, which is the amount that the policyholder has agreed to pay towards any claim. The excess amount can vary based on the policy and can be different for different types of claims.</li>
            <li><strong>Modifications to the vehicle:</strong> If the vehicle has been modified from its original specifications, the insurance policy will not cover damages caused due to the modification.</li>
            <li><strong>Timely renewal:</strong> It is essential to renew the insurance policy before the expiry date to ensure that the policy is in force at all times. If the policy has lapsed, then any damages or accidents that occur during that period will not be covered.</li>
            <li><strong>Unattended vehicle:</strong> Leaving the vehicle unattended with the engine running or with the keys inside can invalidate the insurance policy.</li>
            <li><strong>Unauthorised repairs:</strong> Getting the vehicle repaired at an unauthorised repair centre results in the insurance policy becoming invalid.</li>
            <li><strong>Personal belongings:</strong> The insurance policy does not cover personal belongings left in the vehicle at the time of the accident or theft.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
